Implement Go-native hook system for intercepting and responding to conversation
lifecycle events. Enables custom logic at key interaction points.

Key features:
- HookSystem interface for managing hook registration and execution
- Pattern-based hook matching with wildcard support
- Thread-safe hook operations with concurrent execution support
- Timeout protection for hook execution (30 seconds)
- Comprehensive error handling and graceful fallback

Supported hook events:
- PreToolUse: Before tool execution (inspect/modify/deny)
- PostToolUse: After tool execution (add context/modify results)
- UserPromptSubmit: Before processing user prompts
- Stop: Conversation termination (cleanup/summary)
- SubagentStop: Subagent termination events
- PreCompact: Before history compaction (preserve critical data)

Hook capabilities:
- Continue/Stop behavior control
- Permission update integration
- Context modification support
- Message injection for user communication

Thread-safe implementation suitable for concurrent usage with proper
resource cleanup and timeout protection.

